  "section": "chain-rule",
  "term": "thm:chain-rule",
  "kind": "Theorem",
  "title": "Chain Rule",
  "root": "",
  "statement": "Let $I, J \\subseteq \\mathbb{R}$ be intervals, let $f : I \\to \\mathbb{R}$ and $g : J \\to \\mathbb{R}$, and suppose that $f(I) \\subseteq J$. Let $c \\in I$. If $f$ is differentiable at $c$ and $g$ is differentiable at $f(c)$, then the composition $g \\circ f$ is differentiable at $c$, and\n\\[\n(g \\circ f)'(c) = g'(f(c))\\,f'(c).\n\\]",
